TESTING INFORMATION 

OVERVIEW
    We use CMake/CTest and QEMU to run tests for ARM32 and AArch64. AArch64 tests 
    are restricted to lens at this moment.

STRUCTURE
    tests/
        CMakeLists.txt  - Test registration and build rules
    tests/<component>/
        *.sh            - Generic & arch-specific tests - see naming conventions for more info.
        common.inc      - Shared shell helper functions

RUNNING TESTS
    Run all tests:
        cd build
        ctest

    Run component tests:
        ctest -R "^<component>-"
        ctest -L soul                   # All soul tests (by label(expansion planned when integration tests are included, the above suffices for now.)

    Run architecture-specific tests:
        ctest -R "aarch64

    Run specific test:
        ctest -R "^lens-pie$"

    Verbose:
        ctest -V

WRITING TESTS
    1. Create a new .sh file in tests/<component>
    2. Source common.inc
    3. Use helper functions as they appear in common.inc to compile and verify output

NAMING CONVENTION
    *.sh  
    arch-arm32-*.sh
    arch-aarch64-*.sh
